        {
            "name": "Level 3: Wind Speaker",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Sorcerer",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You know Primordial or another language of your choice. Also, as a Bonus Action you cause one of the following effects until the end of your next turn.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You cause rain to start or stop falling within a 100-foot emanation.",
                        "You make wind blow in a chosen direction within a 100-foot emanation."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Tempestuous Magic",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Sorcerer",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Immediately before or after you cast a Sorcerer spell of level 1+, you can fly up to 10 feet without provoking opportunity attacks and force a creature within 30 feet of you to make a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC or take {@damage 1d6} Lightning damage. At Sorcerer level 6 this damage becomes {@damage 2d6}, {@damage 3d6} at level 14, and {@damage 4d6} at level 18."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Heart of the Storm",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Sorcerer",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "You gain resistance to Lightning and Thunder damage. In addition, when you use your Tempestuous Magic, you can target up to two creatures within 30 feet of you instead of one."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Wind Soul",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Sorcerer",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "You gain 60 feet of Fly speed. As a Magic Action, you can reduce your Fly speed to 30 feet and choose a number of creatures within 60 feet of you equal to your Charisma modifier. The chosen creatures gain 30 feet of Fly speed for 8 hours."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 18: Storm's Fury",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Sorcerer",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 18,
            "entries": [
                "You embody the full might of a storm, you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "You have immunity to Lightning and Thunder damage.",
                        "If you drop to 0 Hit Points and don't die outright, you regain a number of hit points equal to your Sorcerer level. In addition, each creature of your choice within 30-foot emanation must make a Strength saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, a creature takes {@damage 4d6} Thunder damage and is pushed 15 feet from you. On a success, it only takes half that damage. Once you use this feature, you cannot do so again until you finish a Long rest, unless you spend 5 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore the use of it."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Lesser Natural Control",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You learn the {@spell elementalism|xphb} cantrip. Constitution is your spellcasting modifier for it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Storm Aura",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Whenever you activate your Rage, choose Desert, Sea, or Tundra. You extend an aura in a 10-foot Emanation originating from yourself for the duration of your Rage. Your aura has an effect based on your choice:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Desert",
                            "entries": [
                                "Roll a number of d6s equal to your Rage damage bonus and add them together. Each creature of your choice in the aura must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take fire damage equal to the total."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Sea",
                            "entries": [
                                "Roll a number of d8s equal to your Rage damage bonus and add them together. One creature of your choice within your aura must make a Dexterity saving throw, taking lightning damage equal to the total on a failed save."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Tundra",
                            "entries": [
                                "Roll a number of d6s equal to your Rage damage bonus and add them together. One creature of your choice within your aura must succeed on a Strength saving throw or it subtracts the number rolled from the next attack roll or ability check it makes before the end of its next turn."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Storm Soul",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you finish a Long or Short rest, choose one of the following benefits that lasts until you use this feature again.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Desert",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain Resistance to Fire damage, and as a Magic action you can touch a flammable object that isn't being worn or carried and cause it to start burning."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Sea",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain Resistance to Lightning damage, can breathe underwater, and gain a Swim Speed equal to your Speed."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Tundra",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain Resistance to Cold damage. As a Magic action you can touch water to turn an unoccupied 5-foot Cube of it into ice, which melts after 1 minute."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Raging Storm",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "The power of the storm you channel grows mightier, lashing out at your foes. The effect is based on the environment you choose for your Storm Aura.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Desert",
                            "entries": [
                                "When a creature fails its saving throw against your Storm Aura effect, it is engulfed with flames. For 1 minute the target takes {@damage 2d6} fire damage at the start of each of its turns, or until it uses an action to make a Dexterity check against your Rage DC to extinguish the flames."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Sea",
                            "entries": [
                                "When you deal your Storm Aura effect damage, you can choose another creature within 30 feet of the original target. The new target makes the same Dexterity saving throw as the original."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Tundra",
                            "entries": [
                                "When a creature fails the saving throw against your Storm Aura effect, it takes {@damage 2d6} cold damage and its speed becomes 0 until the end of its next turn."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Shielding Aura",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Storm",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "You gain immunity instead of resistance to the damage type of your Storm Soul feature. Moreover, each creature of your choice within a 15-foot Emanation from you gains the benefits of your Storm Soul resistance."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Giant's Power",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Giant",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You know {@language Giant} or another language of your choice, if you already know it. You learn the {@spell druidcraft|xphb} or {@spell thaumaturgy|xphb} cantrip and Strength is your spellcasting modifier for it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Giant's Havoc",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Giant",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Your rage channels the primal might of giants. While raging, you gain the following benefits:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Improved Reach",
                            "entries": [
                                "The reach of your attacks is increased by 5 feet."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Mighty Stature",
                            "entries": [
                                "If you are smaller than Large, you become Large along with anything you are wearing. If you lack the room to become Large, your size doesn't change."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Elemental Cleaver",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Giant",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "You bond with the elemental might of giants to infuse weapons with primordial energy. When you enter your rage, you can give the following benefits to a weapon you're holding.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Primal Power",
                            "entries": [
                                "Choose one of the following damage types: Cold, Fire, Lightning or Thunder. Once every turn, the weapon deals {@damage 1d12} extra damage of the chosen type."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Returning",
                            "entries": [
                                "The weapon gains the thrown property (20/60). If you throw the weapon, it reappears in your hand the instant after it hits or misses a target."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Mighty Impel",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Giant",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "Your strength allows you to hurl creatures on the battlefield. While raging, you can use a Bonus Action to force a Large or smaller creature within your reach to make a Strength saving throw (DC equal to 8 + your Strength modifier + your Proficiency Bonus). On a failed save, you move the creature 5 feet in a direction of your choice, and you can move up to 5 feet in that direction immediately after."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Demiurgic Colossus",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Barbarian",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Giant",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "The primordial power of your rage intensifies. When you rage, your reach increases by 10 feet, your size can increase to Large or Huge (your choice) and the extra damage dealt by your Elemental Cleaver becomes {@damage 2d12}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Psychic Blades",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Bard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Whispers",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Your mastery of psychic magic gives you the following benefits.",
                "You learn the {@spell shadow blade|xphb} spell and it counts as a Bard spell for you.",
                "When you hit with a weapon attack or deal Psychic damage you can expend one use of your Bardic Inspiration to deal extra Psychic damage equal to three rolls of your Bardic Inspiration die."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Words of Terror",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Bard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Whispers",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "If you speak for 1 minute to a creature with an Intelligence ability score of at least 6, you can attempt to seed paranoia in its mind. At the end of the conversation, the target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell DC or it takes {@damage 1d6} psychic damage and becomes {@condition frightened} of you. The {@condition frightened} effect ends if the target ends a turn without seeing you or experiencing harm from you."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Mantle of Whispers",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Bard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Whispers",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When a Medium or Small creature within 30 feet of you reaches 0 hit points, you steal its shadow. You can take a Bonus Action to spend the shadow and gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Dark Resilience",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain temporary hit points equal to your Bard level."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Psychic Whispers",
                            "entries": [
                                "For 1 hour, you take the creature's appearance and learn general details on the creature's background and personal life."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of once) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Mischievous Afterimage",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Bard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Whispers",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "Immediately after you deal damage with your Psychic Blades feature, you can teleport 15 feet to an unoccupied space you can see."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Shadow Lore",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Bard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Whispers",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, you whisper in the mind of a creature within 30 feet of you. It must make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell DC. On a failed save, your whispers sound like the target's own doubts and fears magnified. The target takes {@damage 8d6} psychic damage and becomes {@condition stunned} until the end of its next turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Arcane Lore",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You studied magical theory and secrets of nature, granting you the following benefits. You know either the {@spell druidcraft|xphb} or {@spell prestidigitation|xphb} cantrip. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for it."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Arcane Shot",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You learn to unleash special magical effects with your shots.",
                "{@b Arcane Shot Options.} You learn two Arcane Shot options of your choice from the \"Arcane Shot Options\" of this subclass. You learn an additional Arcane Shot option of your choice when you reach 7th, 10th, 15th, and 18th levels in this class.",
                "{@b Using Arcane Shot.} Once per turn when you make a ranged attack using a weapon with the ammunition property, you can apply one Arcane Shot option to that attack. You decide to use the option when you hit or miss.",
                "{@b Arcane Shot Die.} The dice used by your Arcane Shot Options is a d6. The Arcane Shot Die becomes a d8 at level 10, a d10 at level 15 and a d12 at level 18.",
                "{@b Saving Throws.} If an Arcane Shot option requires a saving throw, the DC equals 8 plus your Intelligence modifier and Proficiency Bonus."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Arcane Shot Options",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "The Arcane Shot options are presented here in alphabetical order.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Banishing Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "The target of the attack takes Psychic damage equal to one roll of your Arcane Shot die and must succeed on a Charisma saving throw or be banished to the Ethereal Plane until the end of its next turn."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Bursting Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "The target of the attack and each creature within a 10-foot emanation originating from it takes Force damage equal to two rolls of your Arcane shot die."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Enfeebling Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "The target of the attack takes Necrotic damage equal to two rolls of your Arcane shot die and must succeed on a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, each damage roll of the target is reduced by the amount of Necrotic damage dealt until the end of its next turn."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Grasping Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "The target of the attack takes Slashing damage equal to one roll of your Arcane Shot Die and must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or have the {@condition restrained} condition for 1 minute."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Piercing Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "You don't make an attack roll for the attack. Each creature in a 30-foot long and 5-foot wide line originating from you must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes Force damage equal to two rolls of your Arcane Shot die."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 7: Curving Shot",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 7,
            "entries": [
                "You learn how to direct an errant arrow toward a new target. If you make an attack roll with a weapon with the ammunition property and miss, you can cause the shot to ricochet as a Bonus Action. Select a new target within 60 feet of the original target and make a new attack roll. On a hit, the new target takes damage equal to one roll of your Arcane Shot die."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 7: Magical Ammunition",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 7,
            "entries": [
                "When you shoot an ammunition, you can imbue it with one of the following properties.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Darkening Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "Magical darkness fills a 15-foot emanation originating from the ammunition for 1 minute."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Unlocking Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "A burst of magic fills a 15-foot emanation originating from the ammunition. Any mundane lock in the emanation becomes unlocked."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Vine Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "A 60-foot long vine grows from the ammunition. You and other creatures can then climb it. The vine withers away after 10 minutes."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Short or Long rest. You can also restore your use of this feature by expending a use of your Second Wind."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Ever-Ready Shot",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "When you roll initiative you can regain one expended use of Arcane Shot."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Arcane Burst",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Indomitable feature, each creature of your choice within a 10-foot emanation originating from you must succeed on a Strength saving throw against your Arcane Shot DC or be pushed 15 feet away from you."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 18: Arcane Evasion",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Arcane Archer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 18,
            "entries": [
                "When a creature misses you with an attack, you can take a reaction to teleport up to 15 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. You can then make a ranged attack roll against the attacker as part of the same reaction."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Elegant Courtier",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: {@skill History}, {@skill Insight}, {@skill Performance}, or {@skill Persuasion}. In addition, whenever you make a Charisma check using a skill you are proficient in, you gain a bonus equal to your Wisdom modifier."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Fighting Spirit",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you take the {@action Attack} Action, you can give yourself advantage on every attack you make in this turn and gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your Fighter level. You can use this feature once, regaining expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 7: Focussed Fighter",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 7,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in Wisdom saving throws. If you already have this proficiency, you instead gain proficiency in Intelligence or Charisma saving throws (your choice)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Rapid Strike",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "Once every turn, as part of the {@action Attack} Action, when you make an attack with advantage, you can forgo the advantage to make an additional weapon attack as part of the same action."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Tireless Spirit",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "When you roll initiative you regain expended uses of Fighting Spirit until you have 2, if you have 1 or fewer."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 18: Strength Before Death",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Fighter",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Samurai",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 18,
            "entries": [
                "When you drop to 0 hit points, you can use your reaction to delay falling {@condition unconscious} and immediately take an extra turn. Taking damage causes death saves failure and can kill you. At the end of this extra turn, you fall {@condition unconscious}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Kensei Weapon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose one melee and one ranged weapon to be your kensei weapons. They can be any weapon that lacks the heavy and special properties, or a Longbow. You are proficient in them, can use their properties with your martial arts features, and they count as monk weapons."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Path of the Kensei",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You gain proficiency in calligrapher's supplies or painter's supplies. In addition, once every turn, you can gain one of the following benefits:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Agile Parry",
                            "entries": [
                                "While you're holding a melee kensei weapon and are not {@condition incapacitated}, you gain a +2 bonus to AC."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei's Shot",
                            "entries": [
                                "When you hit with a ranged kensei weapon as part of the {@action Attack} Action, you can deal extra damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: One with the Blade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "You extend your power into your kensei weapons, granting you the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei Blow",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can make an attack with a kensei weapon as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Deft Strike",
                            "entries": [
                                "Once every turn, when you hit a target with a kensei weapon, you can spend 1 Focus Point to deal extra damage equal to a roll of your Martial Arts die."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 11: Sharpen the Blade",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 11,
            "entries": [
                "At the start of your turn, you can expend up to 3 Focus Points to empower one kensei weapon you touch. That weapon gains a bonus to attack and damage rolls equal the number of discipline points spent until the end of your turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 17: Kensei Master",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Kensei",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 17,
            "entries": [
                "At the peak of your fighting prowess, you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Kensei Flurry",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can expend 1 Focus Point to make two attacks with a Kensei Weapon as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Unerring Accuracy",
                            "entries": [
                                "Your mastery of weapons grants you extraordinary accuracy. If you miss with an attack roll using a monk weapon on your turn, you can reroll it. You can use this feature only once on each of your turns."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Radiant Awakening",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "At the start of your turn, you can spend 1 discipline point to wreathe yourself in radiant energy for 10 minutes. For the duration you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        "Once every turn, when you hit with an attack, you can deal extra radiant damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die.",
                        "Once every turn, you can replace an Unarmed Strike attack to make a ranged attack using Dexterity against a creature within 60 feet of you. If the attack hits, it deals radiant damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Searing Arc Strike",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "As a bonus action, you can spend 1 Focus Point to emit a 15-foot cone of light from your hand. Each creature in the area must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save it takes radiant damage equal to two rolls of your Martial Arts die, or half as much on a successful one."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 11: Searing Sunburst",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 11,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, you hurl a bolt of light at a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in that 20-foot radius sphere centered on that point must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take {@damage 6d6} radiant damage, or half as much on a successful one."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 17: Sun Avatar",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Monk",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Sun",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 17,
            "entries": [
                "You become an avatar of radiant energy. You gain immunity to radiant damage and once per turn when you hit with an attack that deals radiant damage, you can force the target to make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the target is {@condition blinded} until the end of its next turn."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Benign Transposition",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Bonus Action, you teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space that you can see. Alternatively, you can choose a willing creature within 30 feet, you both teleport swapping places. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of one) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Conjuration Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Conjuration school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Conjuration school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Distant Transposition",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "The range of your Benign Transposition feature increases to 60 feet. Additionally, you now regain all expended uses of it when you finish a Short or Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Durable Summons",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast a Conjuration spell to summon or create a creature using a spell slot, that creature gains temporary hit points equal to twice your Wizard level when it first appears. While it has these temporary hit points, the creature has resistance to every damage type except Force, Necrotic, Psychic and Radiant."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Focussed Conjuration",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "Taking damage can’t break your concentration on Conjuration spells."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Splintered Summons",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Conjurer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast {@spell Summon Construct|xphb}, {@spell Summon Dragon|xphb}, {@spell Summon Elemental|xphb} or {@spell Summon Fey|xphb} using a spell slot, you can modify the spell to summon two creatures instead of one. Each creature uses the stat block and rules denoted by the spell and appears in a different unoccupied space of your choice within the spell’s range, but the summoned creatures’ hit points are halved. If you lose concentration on the spell, both creatures disappear."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Enchanting Voice",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Whenever you make a Charisma check, you gain a bonus to the check equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of +1). You also gain proficiency in one of these skills of your choice: {@skill Deception}, {@skill Intimidation} or {@skill Persuasion}."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Enchantment Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Enchantment school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Enchantment school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Hypnotic Presence",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "As a Magic Action, choose one creature that you can see within 30 feet of yourself. If the target can see or hear you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or have the {@condition charmed} condition for 1 minute or until it takes damage. While {@condition charmed} in this way, the target has the {@condition incapacitated} condition and a speed of 0. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Split Enchantment",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Hypnotic Presence feature or cast an Enchantment spell that targets only one creature, you can target one additional creature with it. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once) and regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Instinctive Charm",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "When a creature within 30 feet of you that you can see hits deals damage to you, you can take a Reaction to force it to make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the damage you take is reduced to 0 and another creature of your choice within 30 feet takes the same amount of damage. Once you use this Reaction, you can’t do so again until you finish a Long rest. You can restore your use of this feature by casting an Enchantment spell with a spell slot."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Superior Enchantment",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Enchanter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "When you use your Hypnotic Presence feature or cast an Enchantment spell that causes the {@condition charmed} condition, you can ignore immunities to the {@condition charmed} condition. Once you use this feature, you cannot do so again until you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Necromancy Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Necromancy school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Necromancy school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Necromancy Spellbook",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Your mastery of necromantic lore grants you extra abilities.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Necrotic Resistance",
                            "entries": [
                                "You gain resistance to Necrotic damage."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Grim Harvest",
                            "entries": [
                                "When you cast a Necromancy spell using a spell slot, you can choose an undead creature you can see within 60 feet of you and make it regain hit points equal to the level of the spell slot expended plus your Wizard level."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Undead Familiar",
                            "entries": [
                                "{@spell Find Familiar|xphb} is added to your spellbook. When you cast the spell, you can choose the Skeleton or Zombie forms in addition to the normal forms."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Undead Thralls",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "{@spell Summon Undead|xphb} is added to your spellbook and you always have it prepared. Whenever you cast the spell, the summoned creature gains the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Undead Fortitude",
                            "entries": [
                                "The creature’s hit point maximum and current hit points increase by a number equal to the level of the spell slot used plus your Intelligence modifier."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Withering Strike",
                            "entries": [
                                "Whenever the creature hits with an attack roll, it deals extra damage equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of one)."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Harvest Undead",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "You have learned more secrets about the nuances of life and death. Immediately after you become bloodied but not outright killed, you can take a Reaction to reduce an Undead creature under your control to 0 hit points. You then immediately regain a number of hit points equal to your Wizard level."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Death's Master",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Necromancer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "Abstruse rituals within your spellbook allow you mastery over forces of death. While holding your spellbook you gain the following benefits.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Bolster Undead",
                            "entries": [
                                "As a Bonus Action, an undead creature you have created or summoned within 60 feet of you gains temporary hit points equal to your Wizard level. A creature can gain these temporary hit points only once every 24 hours."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Burst Undead",
                            "entries": [
                                "When an undead creature under your control is reduced to 0 hit points, you can cause it to explode with necrotic energy. Roll a number of d6s equal to your Intelligence modifier and add them together. Each creature in a 10-foot emanation originating from the undead makes a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC. A target takes Necrotic damage equal to the number rolled on a failed save and half as much on a successful one."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Transmutation Savant",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "Choose two Wizard spells from the Transmutation school, each of which must be no higher than level 1 or 2, and add them to your spellbook for free.",
                "In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Transmutation school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Transmuter's Stone",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you finish a Long rest, you can create a magic stone that lasts until you use this feature again. A creature carrying the stone gains proficiency in Constitution saving throws and one of the following benefits chosen when you create the stone.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Darkvision",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains darkvision with a range of 60 feet or increases the range of its darkvision by 60 feet."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Resistance",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains resistance to Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, Poison or Thunder damage (you choose each time you choose this benefit)."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Speed",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer’s speed increases by 10 feet."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "You can change the stone’s benefit when you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Empowered Transmutation",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "When you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot, you can treat the spell as if it were cast using a spell slot 1 level above the slot expended. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long rest."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 6: Potent Stone",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 6,
            "entries": [
                "Your Transmuter’s Stone is more versatile. When you create it, you can choose up to two benefits. You can choose each option other than Resistance only once, and if you choose Resistance twice, you must choose different damage types. You can change either or both benefits when you cast a Transmutation spell using a spell slot. In addition, the following are now among your benefit options for Transmuter’s Stone.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Evasive",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer can take the disengage action as a Bonus Action."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Tremorsense",
                            "entries": [
                                "The bearer gains Tremorsense with a range of 30 feet."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 10: Shapechanger",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 10,
            "entries": [
                "You always have the {@spell Polymorph|xphb} spell prepared and can cast it once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a Long Rest. In addition, when you target yourself with the spell, you can modify the spell to gain the benefits below.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Game Statistics",
                            "entries": [
                                "You retain your personality, memories, and ability to speak. You also retain your Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores; class features; languages; and feats."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Transmute Spells",
                            "entries": [
                                "You can cast Transmutation spells while shapeshifted, except for any spell with a Material component that has a specified cost."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 14: Master Transmuter",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Wizard",
            "classSource": "XPHB",
            "subclassShortName": "Transmuter",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 14,
            "entries": [
                "While you carry your Transmuter’s Stone, you can take a Magic Action to consume the reserve of transmutation magic stored inside and choose one of the following benefits. After you use your Transmuter’s Stone in this way, the stone crumbles to dust. You can prevent the stone’s destruction by expending a level 5+ spell slot.",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Major Transmutation",
                            "entries": [
                                "An object you touch— no larger than a 10-foot Cube or eight connected 5-foot Cubes —and transmute it into another nonmagical object of similar size and mass and of equal or lesser value."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Panacea",
                            "entries": [
                                "A creature you touch regains a number of Hit Points equal to half its Hit Point maximum (round down). Any curse affecting the target is lifted. If the target has the {@condition poisoned} or {@condition petrified} conditions, those conditions end."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Restore Life",
                            "entries": [
                                "You cast the {@spell Raise Dead|xphb} spell without expending a spell slot, using the stone in place of the required Material components."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Restore Youth",
                            "entries": [
                                "A willing creature you touch permanently appears {@dice 3d10} years younger, to a minimum of young adulthood."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
