                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 3: Armor Model",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "When you don your arcane armor, choose one of the following armor models: Guardian or Infiltrator. The model you choose gives you special benefits while you wear it.",
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Guardian",
                    "entries": [
                        "{@b Thunder Gauntlets.} You can use Intelligence instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strikes. You can roll {@damage 1d8} in place of their normal damage and you can deal thunder or bludgeoning damage (your choice) when you deal damage with your unarmed strikes. Also, a creature you hit has disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you until the start of your next turn.",
                        "{@b Defensive Field.} As a bonus action, you can gain temporary hit points equal to your Artificer level. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Infiltrator",
                    "entries": [
                        "{@b Lightning Launcher.} A gemlike node appears on one of your armored fists or on the chest. It is a simple ranged weapon (range 100/300) that uses your Intelligence for attack and damage rolls. On a hit, it deals {@damage 2d6} lightning damage and applies the Vex mastery. Once every turn, on a hit you can deal {@damage 1d6} extra lightning damage.",
                        "{@b Powered Steps.} Your walking speed increases by 10 feet and you gain advantage on Dexterity ({@skill Stealth}) ability checks."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Extra Attack",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "You can attack twice, rather than once, whenever you take the {@action Attack} action."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 9: Armor Modifications",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 9,
            "entries": [
                "Your Arcane Armor counts as separate items for the purposes of your Infuse Items feature: armor, boots, helmet and weapon. Each of those items can bear one of your infusions, and the infusions transfer over if you change your armor's model. Moreover, the number of items you can infuse increases by 2, but those extra items must be part of your Arcane Armor."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 15: Perfected Armor",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Armorer",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 15,
            "entries": [
                "Your Arcane Armor gains additional benefits based on its model, as shown below.",
                {
                    "type": "entries",
                    "name": "Guardian",
                    "entries": [
                        "When a Huge or smaller creature you can see ends its turn within 30 feet of you, you can use your reaction to pull it up to 25 feet directly to an unoccupied space. If you pull the target to a space within 5 feet of you, you can make a melee weapon attack against it as part of this reaction."
