        {
            "name": "Level 3: Eldritch Cannon",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Artillerist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 3,
            "entries": [
                "You learn how to create a magical cannon. Using {@item woodcarver's tools|xphb} or {@item smith's tools|xphb}, you can take an action to magically create a Small or Tiny eldritch cannon in an unoccupied space on a horizontal surface within 5 feet of you. A Small cannon occupies its space; a Tiny one can be held in one hand.",
                "Once you create a cannon, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest or expend a spell slot of level 1 or higher. You can have only one cannon at a time.",
                "The cannon is a magical object with AC 18 and hit points equal to five times your Artificer level. It is immune to Poison and Psychic damage. If forced to make an ability check or saving throw, treat all its ability scores as 10. {@spell Mending|xphb} cast on it restores {@dice 2d6} hit points. It disappears after 1 hour or when reduced to 0 hit points. You can dismiss it early as a Magic action.",
                "When you create the cannon, choose one of the following types:",
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Flamethrower",
                            "entries": [
                                "The cannon exhales fire in a 15-foot Cone. Each creature in the area makes a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC, taking {@damage 2d8} Fire damage on a failed save or half as much on a success. The fire ignites flammable objects not being worn or carried."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Force Ballista",
                            "entries": [
                                "Make a ranged spell attack originating from the cannon at one creature or object within 120 feet. On a hit, the target takes {@damage 2d8} Force damage and is pushed up to 5 feet away from the cannon."
                            ]
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "item",
                            "name": "Protector",
                            "entries": [
                                "The cannon emits positive energy, granting itself and each creature of your choice within 10 feet a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to {@dice 1d8} + your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1)."
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                "On each of your turns, you can take a Bonus Action to activate the cannon if you are within 60 feet of it. As part of the same Bonus Action, you can command it to walk or climb up to 15 feet to an unoccupied space, if it has legs."
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Level 5: Arcane Firearm",
            "source": "AliFosche",
            "className": "Artificer",
            "classSource": "AliFosche",
            "subclassShortName": "Artillerist",
            "subclassSource": "AliFosche",
            "level": 5,
            "entries": [
                "You know how to turn a wand, staff, or rod into an arcane firearm, a conduit for your destructive spells. When you finish a Long Rest, you can use {@item woodcarver's tools|xphb} to carve special sigils into such an item, turning it into your arcane firearm. The sigils disappear if you later carve them on a different item; otherwise they last indefinitely.",
